(3) To compute the correct position of the pivot element, it rearranges the array A[start ...
end] into two subarrays A[start ... p-1] and A[p+1 ... end] such that each element of
A[start ... p-1] is less than or equal to the pivot element and each element of A[p+1 ...
end] is greater than the pivot element. The subarray can be empty.
Here, p indicates the position of the pivot element, and A[start ... end] indicates a
subarray consisting of the elements from index start to index end of array A.
